.TH "edma_alloc_slot" 9 "edma_alloc_slot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
edma_alloc_slot \- allocate DMA parameter RAM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" edma_alloc_slot
.BI "(struct edma_cc *ecc "  ","
.BI "int slot "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ecc" 12
pointer to edma_cc struct
.IP "slot" 12
specific slot to allocate; negative for "any unused slot"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This allocates a parameter RAM slot, initializing it to hold a
dummy transfer.  Slots allocated using this routine have not been
mapped to a hardware DMA channel, and will normally be used by
linking to them from a slot associated with a DMA channel.

Normal use is to pass EDMA_SLOT_ANY as the \fIslot\fP, but specific
slots may be allocated on behalf of DSP firmware.

Returns the number of the slot, else negative errno.
